abstract: NORFOLK, Va., Nov. 2.--Augustus Eason owned a large farm near Hickory Ground, in this county. Last week he posted notices forbidding all persons from trespassing on the same. abstract: WHITE RIVER JUNCTION, Vt., Nov. 4.-- Returns from 140 towns give Blaine 28,241; Cleveland, 12,694; Butler, 578; St. John, 1,168. Blaine's plurality, 15,547. The same towns in 1880 gave Garfield 32,368; Hancock, 13,317; Weaver, 1011; Garfields's plurality 19,051. If the remaining 120 towns give a  proportionate vote to the above, Blaine's majority will be upward of 25,000. The vote for St. John is drawn mostly from the Republicans, while Butler's comes from the Democrats.

abstract: CAMERON, Texas, Nov. 8.--A triple murder was unearthed to-day at Bryant station, 12 miles west of Cameron. abstract: RIO JANEIRO, Nov. 17, via Galveston.-- The steamer Matteo Bruzzo, which left Montevideo with cases of cholera on board, has arrived here. The railroad officials have ordered the army to leave their promises.

abstract: FRANKLIN, Tenn., Nov. 28.--Bill Youngerman made himself obnoxious to a negro congregation last night while drunk.
